-- Canada Won't Rule on BHP-Potash Takeover Bid Today, Harper Spokesman Says
-- B y   A l e x a n d r e   D e s l o n g c h a m p s
-- 2010-11-02T20:34:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-02/canada-won-t-rule-on-bhp-potash-takeover-bid-today-harper-spokesman-says.html
Canada’s government won’t announce a
decision today on whether to approve BHP Billiton Ltd.’s $40
billion hostile bid for Potash Corp. of Saskatchewan Inc., said
Dimitri Soudas, a spokesman for Prime Minister Stephen Harper.  Soudas didn’t say when the announcement would be, speaking
in an interview in Ottawa today. The deadline for a decision is
tomorrow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexandre Deslongchamps in Ottawa at 
 adeslongcham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Greg Quinn at 
 gquinn1@bloomberg.net  